{"TopicId":192392,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Unoccupied orbiting vehicle starts spinning on its own","CreatedByName":"purpleivan","CreatedById":120081,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-14T10:36:04Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"purpleivan","CreatedById":120081,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-14T10:36:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBack in December I had the same problem with a small vehicle in orbit of Eve, but now the issue has struck again, this time in Kerbin orbit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have a vehicle which is unoccupied and has no probe core, but it does have a command seat, that Jeb was sitting in. The vehicle was fine until Jeb left the seat, at which point it started to spin up, getting faster and faster. After a couple of minutes it spinning at multiple revolusions per seconds, and ultimately so fast that it tears itself apart.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen this problem occured before, I thought someone had posted a solution to this (which I can\u0027t find), which I remembered as being to go to the Tracking Station, then back to the vessel, but that doesn\u0027t work.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo... anyone have a solution to this?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf all else fails I\u0027ll edit Jeb back into the seat.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-03-14T10:36:21Z\u0022 title=\u002203/14/2020 10:36  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 14, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by purpleivan\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Hotel26","CreatedById":139095,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-14T10:44:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHmm, big problem.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI do believe though that the ASAT technology to solve your problem may have been researched/deployed last year.\u00A0 Try this:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u002257228\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed7983096025\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/27292-what-did-you-do-in-ksp-today/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=3699682\u0026amp;embedComment=3699682\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment\u0022 style=\u0022height:299px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"purpleivan","CreatedById":120081,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-14T10:49:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223756404\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192392\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221584182671\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022139095\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Hotel26\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, Hotel26 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHmm, big problem.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI do believe though that the ASAT technology to solve your problem may have been researched/deployed last year.\u00A0 Try this:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnti Satellite you say... sounds like another way of break it into bits \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022105.88\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022 width=\u002217\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003EI need to use the vessel as is, as it\u0027s part of a challenge entry.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Hotel26","CreatedById":139095,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-14T10:51:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry.\u00A0 (all sheepish).\u00A0 I am surprised that just getting focus on it and then applying warp (it\u0027s in space, right), wouldn\u0027t halt the rotation...?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"purpleivan","CreatedById":120081,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-14T10:55:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223756408\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192392\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221584183064\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022139095\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Hotel26\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, Hotel26 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry.\u00A0 (all sheepish).\u00A0 I am surprised that just getting focus on it and then applying warp (it\u0027s in space, right), wouldn\u0027t halt the rotation...?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo, tried that. It just starts spinning up again immediately that warp ends.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"purpleivan","CreatedById":120081,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-14T11:52:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOk... the spinning problem has now stopped.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot certain what fixed it, as there was a lot of swapping between vehicles, putting vehicles on the pad then recovering them, before I went back to the vehicle and noticed it had stopped spinning.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-14T17:38:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you have a joystick plugged in, make sure it\u0027s centered.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"purpleivan","CreatedById":120081,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-14T19:48:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223756595\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192392\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221584207526\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002227914\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vanamonde\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Vanamonde said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you have a joystick plugged in, make sure it\u0027s centered.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s not drift on a joystick as I don\u0027t have one plugged in.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve no idea what causes this, or what ultimately stops it... it\u0027s weird and annoying, but at least not that frequent.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-03-14T19:49:18Z\u0022 title=\u002203/14/2020 07:49  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 14, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by purpleivan\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bonyetty","CreatedById":57769,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-15T13:48:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYour trim setting?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u002239989\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed444255503\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/40455-adjusting-the-trim-what-is-it-and-how-do-i-do-this/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:209px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"purpleivan","CreatedById":120081,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-15T21:25:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223756976\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192392\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221584280109\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257769\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022bonyetty\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, bonyetty said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYour trim setting?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe have a winner \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAt first I was about to say \u0022no... nothing to do with trim, there\u0027s no aerodynamics involved\u0022, then read the thread linked to. One quick test later and I can confirm that this was the problem. Fixed by pressing Alt X.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI had no idea there was this functionality in the game.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for that answer, it was begining to drive me nuts not knowing what it was.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-03-15T23:02:53Z\u0022 title=\u002203/15/2020 11:02  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 15, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by purpleivan\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}